Marshmallow Go - Privacy Notice
This privacy notice gives you information about how Marshmallow Financial Services Limited (“
Marshmallow
” “
we
”, “
our
”, “
us
”) collect and use your personal data for Marshmallow Go.
If you would like to speak to our Data Protection Officer you can email
dpo@marshmallow.co
.
Driving behaviour data (acceleration, braking, cornering)
GPS location data
Mobile phone usage (we will know if you’ve been using your phone while driving)
Driving trip datetime data
(together, “
Marshmallow Go Data
”).
Personal data means any data about an individual from which that person can be identified. When you opt into Marshmallow Go, we will collect the following types of personal data:
We will only use Marshmallow Go Data where the law allows us to. The table below explains the purposes for which we intend to use Marshmallow Go Data and the legal bases we rely on for each of these purposes. We have further identified and explained our legitimate interests for doing so. We use Marshmallow Go Data to:
‍
Purpose
Legal Basis
Better understand how our customers drive so we can develop more accurate pricing in our insurance products.
Legitimate Interests - necessary to help us develop more effective pricing models.
Create risk scores about your driving and share these with you.
Legitimate Interests - necessary to provide you with feedback about your driving and give you the opportunity to improve your risk score.
Verify that the information you have provided us in relation to claims is correct for fraud prevention.
Legitimate Interests - necessary to ensure the prevention of fraud where you have made a claim.
Help with your claims process. This may include accident detection and location checks.
Legitimate Interests – (in the event of an accident resulting in a claim) necessary to help us verify the circumstances around the incident.
Automated Decision Making
‍
Marshmallow Go Data will be used by us and our third party partner Sentiance to create a profile of your driving style. This is how we can provide you with driving scores and give you insights about your driving style.
‍
Your driving score is affected by:
– how harshly you brake or accelerate
– how smoothly you corner
– how often you exceed the speed limit and by how much
– how often you use your phone while driving
– the environments you drive in
– the times of you day you drive
‍
