how smoothly you corner
how often you exceed the speed limit and by how much
how often you exceed the speed limit and by how much
how often you use your phone while driving
the environments you drive in
the times of you day you drive
– how harshly you brake or accelerate
– how smoothly you corner
– how often you exceed the speed limit and by how much
– how often you use your phone while driving
– the environments you drive in
– the times of you day you drive
You can always improve your driving score by adopting positive driving behaviours which you can learn about when using Marshmallow Go.
Please note, Marshmallow Go Data will not be used to cancel or calculate renewal premiums for your existing policy with us.
We may share Marshmallow Go Data with other members of the Marshmallow Group and third parties outside of the Marshmallow Group to ensure that we can provide services to you as follows:
1.
Our service provider Sentiance
, who help us to generate and understand your driving score.
2.
Marshmallow Insurance Limited
and/or Wakam
, the companies who underwrite our policies.
3.
Partners
who help us manage claims in the event of one. To see this full list, please contact us at
DPO@marshmallow.co
Whenever we transfer your personal data out of the UK or EU, we ensure a similar degree of protection is afforded to it by ensuring at least one of the following safeguards is implemented:
‍
‍
we will only transfer your personal data to countries that have been deemed to provide an adequate level of protection for  personal data by the UK Secretary of State (for a list please see
A guide to international transfers | ICO
) or European Commission
Data protection adequacy for non-EU countries (europa.eu)
); or
for certain service providers we may use specific contracts approved for use in the UK or EU which give personal data the same protection it has in the UK or EU such as the UK International Data Transfer Agreement (laid before Parliament by the UK Secretary of State on 2 February 2022) or European Commission’s Standard Contractual Clauses issued pursuant to Commission Implementing Decision (EU) 2021/914 of June 4, 2021.
Please contact us if you want further information on the specific mechanism used when we transfer your personal data out of the UK or EU.
Marshmallow Go Data will be stored alongside the personal data we process to underwrite your insurance policy. This is based on a statutory retention period of 7 years.
You can opt-out of Marshmallow Go at any time. However, any Marshmallow Go Data collected whilst you were signed up to Marshmallow Go will be retained for 7 years where you have purchased an insurance policy from us.
You can exercise the below rights in relation to your Marshmallow Go Data. However, there may be some instances where we cannot fulfil your request, either in part or fully. We have provided examples of where this may be the case below:
‍
What are your rights?
Examples of where we might not be able to fulfil your request
Request Deletion
: You can ask us to delete the data we hold about you where:
(i) there is no good reason for us continuing to process it, or
(ii) where you are exercising your right to object to our processing (see below).
Data connected to insurance policies you’ve purchased with us will need to be stored for 7 years. This is based on a statutory requirement we have as an insurance company.
Where we have identified data in relation to potential fraud, we will retain information that is necessary to help us handle this.
Request a copy of your data
: This is commonly known as a “
data subject access request
”. You can ask us to provide you with a copy of the data we hold about you and check that we are lawfully processing it.
We won’t include information relating to other people (including Marshmallow employees).
Data Portability
: You can request for us to send your data to another organisation.
We won’t include information relating to other people (including Marshmallow employees).
Request restriction to processing
: You can ask us to pause using the data we hold about you where:
- you want us to establish the personal data’s accuracy;
- our use of the personal data is unlawful but you do not want us to erase it; or
- you need us to hold the data even if we no longer require it as you need it to establish, exercise or defend legal claims.
We will continue to process the data to enable us to store it.
Object to processing
: You can object to us processing your personal data where we are relying on a legitimate interest and there is something about your situation which makes you want to object to processing on this ground as you feel it impacts on your fundamental rights and freedoms.
We will consider and respond to all requests to stop processing where we use legitimate interests. If we find that your rights as a data subject are not overridden, we may not uphold the request.
Data rectification
: If you find that any data we hold about you is incomplete or inaccurate you can let our Customer Operations team know on our Live Chat and we will update it.
In certain circumstances we may need to run additional verification checks about the contested data.
If you have any questions about this notice or want to make a complaint, please email go to our Complaints Policy section. If you're still not happy you can refer your complaint to the Information Commissioner's Office whose website is: www.ico.org.uk and phone number is 0303 123 1113. Our ICO registration number is ZA295898.
‍
Changes to this notice
‍
We keep this notice under regular review. This version was last updated on 15 February 2024.
